The paper deals with data structures for range queries, which is a fundamental problem in computer science. The focus is on uncertain data, which suggests that the paper may belong to the database (cs.DB) or information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories. However, the use of probability density functions and the three types of queries (top-$1$, top-$k$, and threshold) suggest that the paper may also be relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.SI). Finally, the fact that the paper presents efficient data structures suggests that it may belong to the data structures (cs.DS) sub-category.
